<HL>
   Marketing Brief -- MCA Inc.:
   Geffen Records Is Acquired
   With $500 Million in Stock
</HL>
<DATE>
04/18/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   MCA
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
RECREATION, ENTERTAINMENT, TOYS, MOVIES, PHOTOGRAPHY, SPORTS (REC)
</IN>
<LP>
   MCA Inc., Universal City, Calif., completed the
acquisition of Geffen Records for stock valued at nearly $500
million.
   The entertainment concern issued to music entrepreneur
David Geffen about 921,900 new Series B convertible preferred
shares, which will pay dividends equal to 10 times the rate
of the common dividend, but will carry only one vote a share.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Mr. Geffen also has signed a long-term employment
agreement with MCA to provide for his exclusive services in
the music industry.
</TEXT>
